"title": "7110: body of Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7110: body of christ",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The term refers both to the physical body of Jesus Christ, which was broken on the cross in order that redemption might be accomplished through him, and to the church.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's physical body</h2>\n<h3>His birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3\">ROM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>His bodily needs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:24\">MAT 8:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:38\">MRK 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:23\">LUK 8:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12\">MRK 11:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:18\">MAT 21:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:2\">LUK 4:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:2\">MAT 4:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:6\">JHN 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28\">JHN 19:28</a></p>\n<h2>His physical suffering</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:26\">MAT 27:26</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:15\">MRK 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:1\">JHN 19:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:28-Matt27:30\">MAT 27:28–27:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:17-Mark15:19\">MRK 15:17–15:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:2-John19:3\">JHN 19:2–19:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:44\">LUK 22:44</a></p>\n<h3>His real physical death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:31-John19:37\">JHN 19:31–19:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35\">MAT 27:35</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:24-Mark15:25\">MRK 15:24–15:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:33\">LUK 23:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:23\">JHN 19:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>His burial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:43-Mark15:46\">MRK 15:43–15:46</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:58-Matt27:60\">MAT 27:58–27:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:52-Luke23:53\">LUK 23:52–23:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:38-John19:42\">JHN 19:38–19:42</a></p>\n<h3>His physical resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:37-Luke24:43\">LUK 24:37–24:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:9\">MAT 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:19-John20:20\">JHN 20:19–20:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:27\">JHN 20:27</a></p>\n<h2>The body of Christ symbolised in the Lord's Supper</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26\">MAT 26:26</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22\">MRK 14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19\">LUK 22:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:51-John6:58\">JHN 6:51–6:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:30\">1CO 11:23–11:30</a></p>\n<h2>The church as the body of Christ</h2>\n<h3>Believers as members of the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:5\">ROM 12:4–12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4\">EPH 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:24\">COL 1:24</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as the head of the body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22\">EPH 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's resurrection body is a new temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:19-John2:22\">JHN 2:19–2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:19–2:22</a></p>\n<h2>Life in the body of Christ</h2>\n<h3>Baptism is into the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:13\">1CO 12:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:27\">GAL 3:27</a></p>\n<h3>Believers receive spiritual life through the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:19\">COL 2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16-1Cor10:17\">1CO 10:16–10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15-Eph4:16\">EPH 4:15–4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Believers care for each other in the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:25-1Cor12:26\">1CO 12:25–12:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:25\">EPH 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:29-Eph5:30\">EPH 5:29–5:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:15\">COL 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Believers have different gifts in the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:5\">ROM 12:4–12:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:6–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12-1Cor12:31\">1CO 12:12–12:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:13\">EPH 4:11–4:13</a></p>",
